answers.body_markdown:
`Common.Enums` is a value that exists at runtime, not a type.  To get the type of a value, you can use the [`typeof` type query operator](https://microsoft.github.io/TypeScript-New-Handbook/chapters/types-from-extraction/#typeof):

    interface Test {
        enumName: keyof typeof Common.Enums;  // &quot;Enum1&quot; | &quot;Enum2&quot; | &quot;Enum3&quot;
    }

Hope that helps; good luck!

